Let’s talk about gaining and losing weight…
It’s inevitable, especially during pregnancy and postpartum (pp). Within the past two years, my weight has drastically changed. My lightest being 145lbs pre-pregnancy, my heaviest during pregnancy at 195lbs, and currently I am 155lbs. for the first 10 months of postpartum, as some of you may know, I just focused on eating healthy and getting stronger, not losing weight. But once I hit 10 months, I decided to join in on one of the six week challenges that I host bi-monthly. I completed two challenges in 12 weeks and lost a total of 25 pounds of fat and gain 5 pounds of muscle. I also added supplements back into my routine, OXYshred being one of my favorites, and the one that helped the most with weight loss. after I finished the two challenges, I focus on building strength and getting stronger by lifting heavier weights. This lead me to my current weight at 155lbs and I feel so strong! 

I remember that feeling of being weak right after having a baby, and it was mentally and physically draining to go through. Pregnancy and postpartum can feel very lonely at times, like the rest of the world is progressing and you are stuck in the same place or getting bigger. I remember my first workout during postpartum was so hard, I had no more core strength, I had to pee every second, especially if I tried to jump, and I remember wishing that I could be strong again, and close to my prepregnancy weight, but I knew it was going to take time and consistency. I’m so proud of my body for going through everything that it did these past two years. Trust me when I say it may seem impossible at first, but with the right program, the right meal plan, the best support team, and belief in yourself to just keep going even when it feels hard, you will make progress.

I’m new to this healing journey and am learning along the way. I started wearing sunscreen everyday on my face in high school because my mom told me it would protect my skin and help me not get brown spots 😵‍💫 and though i can’t turn back time, i would tell my younger self to focus on wearing protective clothing, eating a high alkaline diet (whole fruits, smoothies and juices), and using a more holistic approach like using natural sunscreen.

The sun is the most natural and readily absorbable way to get vitamin d. we need vitamin d to have a properly functioning body!!! the hormone that comes from vitamin d allows our cells to function. it help us absorb calcium, minerals and nutrients to build strong bones. it’s so powerful and so easy to get ☀️

Studies have shown that 99% of women with fibroids have a vitamin d deficiency as well as people with a mental illness and lupus 🥺 If that resonates with you or if you are sensitive to sunlight, I recommend starting to get sunlight for short periods of time and working your way up to 10-20 minutes. Practice breathing and meditating to pass the time! 

When you become more alkaline you will start to notice how much more sun you can tolerate too. The more I learn about this way of living, the more I will share!!! 

#holistichealing #sunlight #sun #healthyself #healthyfood #alkaline #detox #changefate #athleticwear

“It’s never too late to change your fate” ✨ Hi Everyone! It’s been a while so let me reintroduce myself ✨ 
1. My name is Lauren and I’m a mom, fitness trainer, educator, athlete and marketing director! 
2. I’m currently doing a 12 week detox to rid my mind, body, and spirit of toxins. I consume warm lemon water, celery juice, smoothies, juices, whole fruits 🍉 and in the evening I have lentil soup, veggies and mashed potatoes 👩🏻‍🍳
3. My favorite snack right now is watermelon but the season is ending and it’s hard to find 🥲 
4. I take a lot of herbs now and am learning more about living holistically 🤍
5. A few things I do everyday now include oil pulling, using a neti pot, doing enemas, and going to the steam room or sauna and I feel AMAZING
6. I’ve always been into fitness but after high school sports my journey officially started in college when I became a distributor for a nutrition company. I started hosting group workouts at school and shared my knowledge about wellness. 
7. I competed in a bikini competition in 2018 and started this IG to post my progress. 
8. I became an online trainer in 2019, right when I graduated from my Masters at USC in film. It was perfect timing because during COVID online fitness was thriving! I also became an athlete for @changefateactivewear which was one of the most exciting parts of my journey because @anacheri was my first fitness idol. Being able to work with her really helped me in all aspects of my life and business. 
9. I became a mom in 2021 and was a working SAHM for Levi’s first 2 years of life. 
10. I nanny part time, and in 2023 I became an in person trainer at the gym, a teacher in the public school system, and the marketing director for @kimithbrand 💫 

This journey has been beautiful and complex. I’ve run into a lot of hurdles this year and a lot of it had to do with the hormonal changes that come after breastfeeding. It hasn’t been easy but I’m so grateful for the support I’ve received from my family and friends. Whether you have been here since day one or you are new to my page, thank you for your support too 🌼 and thank you for being here!
